Ilon Musk is forced to leave the post of head of Tesla Board of Directors
The US Securities and Exchange Commission and Tesla ’ s founder , Ilon Musk , settled their dispute over fraud .
This is reported by CNBC News .
According to the TV channel , within the framework of the agreements reached Masku will have to leave the post of the head of the board of directors of Tesla .
At the same time , the commission allowed Mask to retain the position of head of Tesla .
As noted , the founder of Tesla will also have to pay an administrative fine of $ 20 million .
The same amount will be charged to Tesla .
At the same time , the money will be distributed among the affected investors .
In addition , the company must appoint two independent directors .
Ilon Musk is an American businessman who is on the list of 50 richest people on the planet according to Forbes magazine .
He is the head of SpaceX Space Corporation , Neuralink Neurotheological Company and the developer of Tesla electric cartels , as well as the co-founder of Paypal .
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission had previously sued Tesla CEO Ilon Mask because of his tweeted announcement about the possible buyback of the company .
Last month , Musk announced plans to make Tesla a private company and buy back all shares on the stock exchange at a fixed price of $ 420 .
The stock price of $ 420 was established allegedly " because of the significance of this number in the marijuana culture " , reported earlier Bloomberg agency citing the co-director of the security department of the commission Stephen Peikin .
At the same time , Ilon Musk subsequently abandoned his plans to redeem the shares .
Commenting on the lawsuit filed against him by the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission , the businessman said that he considered the charges of fraud unfounded , and added that he was very disappointed and saddened by these claims .
" Honesty is the most important value in my life , and the facts will prove that I in no way violated it , " the businessman said in an interview with CNBC .
In August , a group of Tesla shareholders filed a collective lawsuit against Mask , complaining about the financial losses incurred .
The plaintiffs claimed that the positions of the businessman had caused them losses .
In particular , one shareholder stated that tweets of the businessman were misleading , which led Tesla stock sellers to purchase papers at artificially high prices to cover their positions .
Other plaintiffs also noted that Ilon Mask 's careless remarks led to sharp fluctuations in the course .
In September , Ilona Maska accused the head of the research company Citron Research of exchange fraud .
In the meantime , if Musk could not resolve his dispute with the US Securities and Exchange Commission , he would be threatened with being suspended from the company ’ s management and even a prison .
The former chairman of the commission Harvey Pitt said this to CNBC TV .
Mask is " a good guy who does not know how to manage a car company . "
