Kosachev : At the 73rd session of the UN General Assembly , the topic of Russia was almost absent in a negative way
The head of the Federation Council Committee on International Affairs Konstantin Kosachev considers the 73rd session of the UN General Assembly successful for Russia and does not exclude that it will be able to become a turning point in the perception of the Russian Federation as an integral participant in the solution of global problems .
" The uniqueness of this 73rd session , in my opinion , is that the rhetoric that we have become almost accustomed to in recent years with regard to Russia has now been much more muted , " said the senator in an interview published on Sunday by the Russian newspaper .
He explained that in previous years the Russian Federation sometimes " identified as one of the three main threats to mankind , then along with Ebola , then along with climate change or terrorism , Russia was in this series , at least in the statement of a group of Western countries , which in this regard expressed quite unanimously " .
At the 73rd session , Kosachev stressed , " Russia 's topic was virtually absent in a negative way . "
" If I carefully analyze the speech of the President of the United States , the President of France , the speech of the German Foreign Minister , I now do not take Ukraine , Georgia , or the British , in any case , the choir was not exactly , " the politician said , noting that Russia " was no longer a wall , about which punch trains " .
The head of the relevant committee of the Security Council does not rule out that this is indicative of a trend which , in his opinion , " will single out the current session of the [ UN General Assembly ] , although this trend may fully manifest itself in a year , two or three " .
" I do not rule out that this session in a sense can be a turning point , " Kosachev admitted , explaining that " there are too many examples of how Russia can move forward in international affairs with its involvement " .
As an example , he cited the situations in Syria , around Iran and North Korea .
“ Unfortunately , this is not Ukraine yet , but I have no doubt that the Russian vision of the Ukrainian crisis will also be in demand over time , ” added the parliamentarian .
This is due to the fact , he believes , that there is " an adequate , sound perception of Russia as not just a possible - an integral participant in solving the global problems of the present day " .
" I don 't want to make a mistake , but I have a feeling that we are going through a point where the movement will no longer be a reversal , it will be a move forward , " he added .
Kosachev called another " interesting and important feeling " in this context " a request for a Russian vision of how the modern world should develop . "
" I attended very many meetings of the head of the Russian delegation [ at the session of the General Assembly ] of Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov , I held my own meetings , and I saw with great pleasure that if a year or two or five years ago Russian opinion , the Russian vision of what is happening in the world , by and large , nobody was interested , then now the situation is different , " said the Chairman of the Committee of the Council .
In his opinion , this is due to the fact that " the so-called new liberal order , which represents the West , has no answers to questions on how to solve world problems due to the obvious lack of ideas in the global space , lack of ideas on how to solve the problems of the Middle East , problems of terrorism , problems of non-proliferation of nuclear weapons , problems of migration " .
" And here the request for a Russian vision becomes more and more obvious , " Kosachev expressed confidence , stressing that in this sense " this session is successful for the work of the Russian delegation , successful for Russia . "
