The main Macedonian oppositionist refused to vote in the referendum
In Macedonia , on Sunday , September 30 , a referendum is being held on an intergovernmental treaty with Greece on renaming the Republic of Macedonia .
Citizens are asked to answer one question : " Do you support EU and NATO membership by accepting an agreement between the Republic of Macedonia and the Hellenic Republic ? "
However , Christian Mickowski , leader of the leading opposition party , the Inner Macedonian Revolutionary Organization , the Democratic Party for Macedonian National Unity ( VMRO-DPMNE ) , said that he would not vote in the referendum .
As the party ’ s spokesman Naum Stoilkovsky explained , Mickoski decided to abstain from voting in order to express his disagreement with the treaty , which considers " harmful " .
According to the spokesperson , the current referendum will decide on renaming the country and not more , while the strategic goal of the party is to achieve membership in NATO and the EU .
A week ago , Macedonian President Gheorghe Ivanov refused to participate in the referendum on September 30 .
He explained that the name for the country he chose 27 years ago in the referendum on independence . The Macedonian leader considers renaming the country a negative factor .
“ A new semi-sovereign state with a new name is being created , ” said Ivanov .
The agreement on the new official name of the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia , the Republic of Northern Macedonia , was signed by the Ministers of Foreign Affairs of Macedonia and Greece on 17 June this year during a solemn ceremony on the shore of the Prespa Lake , which is the border between the two countries .
This treaty should resolve the long-standing dispute over the name of the country , as well as Skopje ’ s way to NATO and the EU , reminiscent of TASS .
